How can we develop and hone feels for system design and implementation (softwares, devices and appliances)? Of course, mastering basic creation skills is important. However, to maximize the accumulated know-how, we must have an ability to get through the details to the heart of a matter. This ability comes with practice to watch and touch real artifacts, and to tear down and investigate them.

